prompt: ""We've been tracking this for several weeks now
response\r: working with Jay Chickerneo and Jeff Marquis. To this point we've been operating under the assumption that the errors experienced are Signal or Wifi/network infrastructiure related.  For the past week we have had active network debugs running for 2 devices in effort to ascertain the root-cause.  Since ~Oct 10 these devices have not had any reports of disconnects. (WIN 417 and WIN 415 are currently tracked.)

prompt: We've made some initial investigations but we haven't found any concrete evidence to go on to make any specific changes.  I've done a survey and confirmed that signal levels appear to be within tolerance across the plant.  The areas where events are occurring should have more

response\r: most of these events are reported to have occurred in areas that have direct line-of-sight to installed APs.   So we're currently stuck until we can capture and analyze some detailed debug information from an event or two.

prompt: The events appear to be more likely to occur in the morning
response\r: centered around 9:00AM EST.

prompt: The events appear to be more likely to occur when running ZProdStage transactions.
Often the events are preceeded by very slow transaction response times and application hangs.
I've attached an updated copy of incident tracker I've been compiling.
There is an open service desk incident under INC0121368.""
